21\/11\/22\/salaf-fatawa\/","url_meta":{"origin":25787,"position":0},"title":"Salaf on Fatwa: Hesitancy in legal verdicts unless necessary","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 22, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Mu\u2019afa ibn \u2018Imran reported: Sufyan al-Thawri, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cI met the jurists and they disliked to answer a question or a request for a legal verdict. They would not issue a legal verdict unless no one else could be found, then they would give their\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":20082,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/12\/08\/fatwa-dislike-halal-haram\/","url_meta":{"origin":25787,"position":1},"title":"Shafi\u2019i on Fatwa: Scholars disliked to say Halal or Haram","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 8, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Shafi\u2019i reported: Abu Yusuf, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cI know our elders among the scholars would dislike to say in their verdicts that this is lawful and this is unlawful, unless it was clearly found in the Book of Allah Almighty, without needing to be explained.\u201d Ibrahim\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":759,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/05\/06\/knowledge-death-scholars\/","url_meta":{"origin":25787,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Scholars: Knowledge disappears with death of &#8216;Ulama","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 6, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Amr reported: The\u00a0Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said,\u00a0\u201cVerily, Allah does not withhold knowledge by snatching it away from his servants, but rather he withholds knowledge by taking the souls of scholars, until no scholar remains and people follow ignorant leaders. They are asked and\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33788,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/11\/20\/tawus-on-moderation\/","url_meta":{"origin":25787,"position":3},"title":"Tawus on Moderation: Tawus steers people towards a middle way","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 20, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Layth reported: Tawus, may Allah have mercy on him, if the people became too strict in a matter, he would grant them a concessions in it. If the people became too permissive in a matter, he would make them be more strict in it. Layth said, \u201cThat is truly knowledge.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":21031,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2015\/10\/13\/fatwa-hikmah-ibn-abbas\/","url_meta":{"origin":25787,"position":4},"title":"Ibn Abbas on Fatwa: Wisdom in issuing legal verdicts","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 13, 2015","format":false,"excerpt":"Sa\u2019d ibn 'Ubaydah reported: A man came to Ibn Abbas, may Allah be pleased with him, and he said, \u201cIs there repentance for one who kills a believer?\u201d Ibn Abbas said, \u201cNo, there is nothing but Hellfire.\u201d After the man left, those sitting nearby said to him, \u201cWhat is this?\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33710,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/10\/13\/sufyan-rukhsah\/","url_meta":{"origin":25787,"position":5},"title":"Sufyan on Fatwa: Granting proper concessions, not strictest opinion","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 13, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Usamah reported: Sufyan al-Thawri, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cIndeed, knowledge in our view is granting a proper concession upon a reliable basis. As for giving the strictest opinion, anybody can do that well.\u201d Source: Ja\u0304mi\u2019 Baya\u0304n al-\u2018Ilm 1467 \u0639\u0646 \u0623\u0628\u064a \u0623\u064f\u0633\u064e\u0627\u0645\u064e\u0629 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0633\u064f\u0641\u0652\u064a\u064e\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u062b\u0651\u064e\u0648\u0652\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0651 \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/25787","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"